          <title>White Sox sweep Angels, keep history on hold as they head to Detroit</title>
          <description><![CDATA[The Chicago White Sox ended a three-game sweep of the Los Angeles Angels with a 7-0 victory, avoiding setting the modern MLB record for losses in a single season, while Chris Flexen pitched 6.1 innings of shutout baseball to notch his third win of the year.]]></description>
